Stocks in South Africa Gain: Blue Label, MiX Telematics, Net1, Telkom Move

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-06-13T15:43:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/stocks-in-south-africa-fall-for-second-day-mix-telematics-telkom-sa-move.html
The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index
rose 12.23, or less than 0.1 percent, to 31,176.58 by the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Blue Label Telecoms Ltd. (BLU)  , a phone-services
reseller, fell to the lowest level since Sept. 10, dropping 12
cents, or 2.2 percent, to 5.35 rand. The company said it has
decided to terminate its business activities in  Nigeria 
following the cancellation of its contract with Multi-Links.  MiX Telematics Ltd. (MIX)  , a company that installs
devices used to track stolen vehicles, jumped 5 cents, or 4.2
percent, to 1.25 rand, the highest level since May 17. The
company increased its dividend payout by 20 percent to 6 cents
in the year through March, it said in a statement today.  Net 1 UEPS Technologies Inc. (NT1)  (NT1 SJ), a payment-systems
provider, dropped the most since March 22, declining 5.10 rand,
or 8.9 percent, to 52 rand. The company said  South Africa ’s
Constitutional Court dismissed its leave to appeal a judgment
allowing a client to contract business to one of its
competitors.  Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TKG SJ), Africa’s largest fixed-
line telephones operator, declined for a second day, losing 25
cents, or 0.7 percent, to 36.80 rand. The company said its sale
of the CDMA technology business of its Nigerian unit will not go
ahead as some precedent conditions have not been met, according
to a regulatory filing today. Earnings for the year through
March fell 35 percent to 4.44 rand a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
